{"title": "Indian To-day", "description": "Based in part upon the author's own observations and personal knowledge, it was the aim of the book to set forth the status and outlook of the North American Indian. He addressed issues such as Indian schools, health, government policy and agencies, and citizenship in this book. In connection with his writings, Eastman was in steady demand as a lecturer and public speaker with the purpose of interpreting his race to the present age. (Summary in part from \"The Indian To-day\" by Charles A. Eastman)", "duration": 14288, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "3473", "name": "Charles Alexander Eastman"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt25/indian_today_1211.jpg", "copyright_year": "1915", "genres": ["Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lucretia B."}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Phil Chenevert"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Charlotte Duckett"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Biographical Note", "readers": [7171], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/theindianto-day_1211_librivox/indiantoday_00_eastman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 356}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1 - The Indian as He Was", "readers": [7247], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/theindianto-day_1211_librivox/indiantoday_01_eastman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1311}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2 - The How and the Why of Indian Wars", "readers": [7534], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/theindianto-day_1211_librivox/indiantoday_02_eastman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1016}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3 - The Agency System: Its Uses and Abuses", "readers": [7640], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/theindianto-day_1211_librivox/indiantoday_03_eastman_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1050}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 4 - The New Indian Policy", "readers": [6670], "path": "https:/